  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated lifesaving treatment and prevention of acute malnutrition among children under five and pregnant and lactating women in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will improve access and provide nutrition services to children aged 0 to 59 months and pregnant and lactating women with acute malnutrition through detection and treatment in nutrition sites. There will be an additional focus on training volunteers in the identification and referral of malnutrition cases to nutrition centres  and mothers trained to examine children to enlarge coverage with close monitoring to prevent wrong referrals and ensure quality of the screening and understanding of the community; provision of outpatient therapeutic feeding services for children aged 6-59 months with severe acute malnutrition and targeted supplementary feeding programme for moderately acute malnourished children and pregnant and lactating women through mobile outreach teams.</narrative>
  </description>
